'''srammap''' - Template for SRAM (Save RAM) map tables on games.darkrepos.com

==Description==

This template creates standardized SRAM map tables documenting battery-backed save data. SRAM is the non-volatile memory used for game saves.

==Usage==

===Basic Usage===
<pre>
{{srammap}}
</pre>

===With Parameters===
<pre>
{{srammap
| platform = NES
| size = 8192
| slots = 3
| description = Custom description text
}}
</pre>

==Parameters==

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Required !! Default !! Description
|-
| platform || No || — || Platform name (NES, SNES, GBA)
|-
| size || No || — || Total SRAM size in bytes
|-
| slots || No || — || Number of save slots
|-
| checksum || No || — || Checksum algorithm used (if known)
|-
| description || No || (standard text) || Custom description for the page
|}

==Table Columns==

The generated table includes these columns:
* '''Offset''' - SRAM offset (hex)
* '''Length''' - Size in bytes
* '''Type''' - Data type
* '''Description''' - What the data stores

==Common SRAM Data Types==

* Player stats and attributes
* Inventory and equipment
* Story progress flags
* Map/exploration data
* Quest completion status
* Game settings/options
* Checksums for data validation

==Example Output==

{{srammap|platform=NES|size=8192|slots=3}}

| $0000 || $0800 || — || Save Slot 1
|-
| $0800 || $0800 || — || Save Slot 2
|-
| $1000 || $0800 || — || Save Slot 3
|-
|}

===Save Slot Structure===
| $0000 || 16 || string || Player name
|-
| $0010 || 2 || word || Current HP
|-
|}

